The premise has merit, even though it's covering well-trod ground. I would've preferred to see the game play out without Foundation intervention, right now the reason who or whatever sent those balls through the tunnel isn't explored thoroughly enough to merit being part of the article, and it would be far more fun if the giant balls of granite caused some mayhem and destruction. This holds back on all the details that might make it fun and replaces them with the Foundation doing things that don't make sense and a pretty lousy 05 note.








